No, no, no.

11:27.947 --> 11:29.180
We're not fighting;
we're just...

11:29.182 --> 11:30.615
having a conversation.

11:30.617 --> 11:32.316
All right.

11:32.318 --> 11:35.186
We're listening
to a really fun <i> conversation</i>

11:35.188 --> 11:38.356
between my costar
from <i> Serial Ape-ist 2</i>

11:38.358 --> 11:40.024
and her fiancé,
who doesn't believe

11:40.026 --> 11:42.526
women should have dreams.

11:44.430 --> 11:47.632
Give me back that juice.

11:48.568 --> 11:50.434
What is the harm
if I audition?

11:50.436 --> 11:51.836
Well, what if you get it?

11:51.838 --> 11:53.938
I don't know, I make a movie,

11:53.940 --> 11:55.573
become rich and famous,

11:55.575 --> 11:56.774
win an Oscar, a Golden Globe

11:56.776 --> 11:58.809
and live an incredibly
wonderful life.

11:58.811 --> 12:01.512
From a Kevin Smith movie?

12:02.582 --> 12:04.882
KEVIN:
Oh, I'm hanging up now.

12:04.884 --> 12:06.250
Don't you listen
to him, buddy.

12:06.252 --> 12:07.485
You're awesome.

12:07.487 --> 12:09.487
You're one of the greatest
directors of our time.

12:09.489 --> 12:12.189
I don't have
a part for you, Wheaton.

12:12.992 --> 12:14.992
And that was Kevin Smith.

12:14.994 --> 12:17.361
Thanks a lot.

12:17.363 --> 12:18.963
I'm just trying to protect you.

12:18.965 --> 12:21.232
How many times did I see you
get your heart broken

12:21.234 --> 12:23.067
trying to make it
as an actress?

12:23.069 --> 12:24.702
Okay, instead of protecting me,
why don't you try

12:24.704 --> 12:26.504
being excited when
something good happens?

12:26.506 --> 12:28.773
I'm always excited for you!

12:28.775 --> 12:30.508
I'm excited that you found
this new job

12:30.510 --> 12:31.976
where you're making
decent money.

12:31.978 --> 12:34.178
Decent? I make twice
what you make.

12:34.180 --> 12:35.880
Wait, twice?!

12:35.882 --> 12:37.548
Yeah.

12:37.550 --> 12:41.218
Like, "times two" twice?

12:42.288 --> 12:44.355
For those of you at home,
Leonard just found out

12:44.357 --> 12:47.591
his fiancée makes
way more money than he does.

12:47.593 --> 12:49.994
Let's listen.

12:49.996 --> 12:51.963
I went to school
for half my life.

12:51.965 --> 12:53.030
I have a doctorate.

12:53.032 --> 12:55.700
I'm still paying off
college loans.

12:55.702 --> 12:56.801
Well, how much do you owe?

12:56.803 --> 12:58.903
Maybe I can help you out.

13:00.640 --> 13:03.908
Wil, can we just turn off
the podcast for a little bit?

13:03.910 --> 13:05.376
For those of you at home,

13:05.378 --> 13:07.678
I am shaking my head "no."

13:15.088 --> 13:16.487
How's it going, Sheldon?

13:16.489 --> 13:19.190
Wonderful!

13:20.026 --> 13:22.193
I just finished
hanging the lights.

13:22.195 --> 13:23.394
Can I come in?

13:23.396 --> 13:25.262
Yes, oh,
but enter through the side.

13:25.264 --> 13:28.332
Batman is
a load-bearing blanket.

13:32.538 --> 13:34.638
Amazing.

13:34.640 --> 13:36.140
I know.

13:36.142 --> 13:37.508
This isn't the printout.

13:37.510 --> 13:39.410
This is my real face.

13:40.513 --> 13:42.013
What are we doing?

13:42.015 --> 13:43.314
This is a fort.

13:43.316 --> 13:45.783
Let's sit on the floor.

13:45.785 --> 13:47.952
Roughing it? Okay.

13:50.189 --> 13:51.689
(gasps)

13:51.691 --> 13:54.892
Everything looks
so big from down here.

13:56.162 --> 13:59.397
This must be
how Leonard feels.

14:02.769 --> 14:04.335
I'm surprised
you could hear me

14:04.337 --> 14:06.404
with this Thin Mint
in your ear!

14:06.406 --> 14:07.805
(laughs)

14:07.807 --> 14:09.473
Yeah, pretty cool, huh?

14:09.475 --> 14:10.441
Yeah.

14:10.443 --> 14:14.378
Anyway,
I should probably get going.

14:14.380 --> 14:15.713
Howie, have you
noticed how often

14:15.715 --> 14:18.482
people say that
when you start to do magic?

14:19.152 --> 14:21.685
Sorry, I have a long drive.

14:21.687 --> 14:24.522
Well, I hope I get
to see you again.

14:24.524 --> 14:26.123
(chuckles)
I hope so, too.

14:26.125 --> 14:29.960
I've always dreamed of having
a brother to play catch with.

14:30.797 --> 14:32.630
Keep dreaming.

14:33.332 --> 14:34.665
Hey, I threw out the first pitch

14:34.667 --> 14:36.534
at an Angels game.
Wow.

14:36.536 --> 14:39.270
He did it with a robot.

14:40.073 --> 14:42.973
You had sex with a robot?

14:42.975 --> 14:45.142
That's not what she meant.

14:45.144 --> 14:46.777
But technically, yes.

14:49.482 --> 14:50.981
Hang on, if you're making
all this money,

14:50.983 --> 14:52.616
where is it?

14:52.618 --> 14:53.751
In a safe place.

14:53.753 --> 14:55.286
What does that mean,
under your bed?

14:55.288 --> 14:56.654
No, it means

14:56.656 --> 14:59.023
a diversified portfolio
of stocks and bonds.

14:59.025 --> 15:00.424
I'm not overly conservative.

15:00.426 --> 15:04.061
I'm young, so my guy said I
can afford to take some risks.

15:04.063 --> 15:06.664
Wait a minute, you have "a guy"?

15:06.666 --> 15:07.965
Don't you have a guy?

15:07.967 --> 15:11.202
Why would I have a guy?
I don't have any money!

15:11.871 --> 15:13.170
Oh, sweetie,

15:13.172 --> 15:15.606
you should really
get some money.

15:15.608 --> 15:17.842
For those of you listening
at home,

15:17.844 --> 15:20.845
how great is this?

15:20.847 --> 15:23.647
Wil, I'm begging you,
just please turn that off.

15:23.649 --> 15:26.283
Sure.

15:26.285 --> 15:28.352
And we're back.

15:28.354 --> 15:31.755
Leonard, why are you making
such a big deal out of this?

15:31.757 --> 15:34.391
So our roles have changed a bit
over the last couple years.

15:34.393 --> 15:35.759
This is the way life is.

15:35.761 --> 15:38.028
And I'm sure in time
they'll change again.

15:38.030 --> 15:41.298
Great, you're not only
more successful than me,

15:41.300 --> 15:43.367
now you're more mature.

15:43.369 --> 15:45.569
Okay, look, would it
make you feel better

15:45.571 --> 15:48.873
if I did something dumb like
sneak out of work one day

15:48.875 --> 15:51.509
to go audition for
a Kevin Smith movie?

15:51.511 --> 15:53.844
That would be great, thank you!

15:55.047 --> 15:56.413
I'm just gonna jump
in here real quick.

15:56.415 --> 15:57.882
Leonard, a moment ago,

15:57.884 --> 16:01.118
you were dead set against Penny
resuming her acting career,

16:01.120 --> 16:02.620
but now you're all for it.

16:02.622 --> 16:05.990
Is it fair to say that
she played you like a violin?

16:07.193 --> 16:09.493
Yes, it is, Wil.

16:12.131 --> 16:14.165
So, I have to ask,

16:14.167 --> 16:16.567
was the robot sexy?

16:16.569 --> 16:18.669
(chuckles)
It was actually

16:18.671 --> 16:21.438
just a mechanical hand.

16:21.440 --> 16:24.708
'Cause that's all
you need, right?

16:25.845 --> 16:27.178
You are my brother.

16:29.315 --> 16:31.882
Okay, so the final four forts

16:31.884 --> 16:34.451
in the first annual
best fort ever contest,

16:34.453 --> 16:36.520
or "fort off," are...

16:37.657 --> 16:38.956
...Fort Knox,

16:38.958 --> 16:40.424
Fort Ticonderoga,

16:40.426 --> 16:42.927
Fort Sumter and...

16:42.929 --> 16:45.196
Fort Cozy McBlanket.

16:46.532 --> 16:47.798
I'd say...

16:47.800 --> 16:49.767
Knox over Ticonderoga

16:49.769 --> 16:50.868
'cause it's got the gold.

16:50.870 --> 16:52.770
Mm-hmm.
And McBlanket over Sumter

16:52.772 --> 16:55.573
'cause it has
a higher thread count.

16:56.309 --> 16:58.275
(phone rings)
Oh.

16:58.277 --> 17:00.978
10:00.

17:00.980 --> 17:02.146
Date night's over.

17:02.148 --> 17:03.414
Wait, no.

17:03.416 --> 17:04.915
We haven't picked a winner.

17:04.916 --> 17:07.384
We both know
this one's gonna win.

17:07.386 --> 17:09.153
Well, of course we do.

17:09.155 --> 17:10.921
Fort Knox doesn't have a secret

17:10.923 --> 17:13.089
physics lending library.

17:14.660 --> 17:16.227
Come on, I'll help
you take this down.

17:16.229 --> 17:17.294
Well, wait.

17:17.296 --> 17:19.363
What if, just this once,

17:19.365 --> 17:21.699
we suspend
the date night parameters

17:21.701 --> 17:24.468
and you stay later?

17:26.305 --> 17:30.341
Well, as long as we're
suspending the parameters,

17:30.343 --> 17:31.942
I could stay really late

17:31.944 --> 17:35.312
and we could have
our first sleepover.

17:35.314 --> 17:37.615
That's a big step.

17:37.617 --> 17:40.784
It's a big fort.

17:42.388 --> 17:43.988
Very well.

17:43.990 --> 17:46.824
I will agree
to a family-friendly,

17:46.826 --> 17:49.627
G-rated, boy-girl sleepover.

17:51.664 --> 17:52.963
PG.

17:52.965 --> 17:56.400
Some scenes may be too intense
for younger viewers.

17:56.402 --> 17:58.636
G-rated,

17:58.638 --> 18:01.739
with a warning for families
with babies and toddlers.

18:04.043 --> 18:05.876
You got yourself a sleepover.

18:07.146 --> 18:08.412
Do you need to borrow

18:08.414 --> 18:09.780
a toothbrush or pajamas?

18:09.782 --> 18:11.749
Would it alarm you to know

18:11.751 --> 18:14.485
that I hid those things here
two years ago

18:14.487 --> 18:16.720
just in case this ever came up?

18:18.958 --> 18:20.190
It would,

18:20.192 --> 18:23.127
but you know how much
I admire preparedness.

18:24.864 --> 18:26.530
How did you know we'd be
in the living room?

18:26.532 --> 18:29.366
Who says this is
the only one I hid?

18:42.877 --> 18:45.043
Hello? What is this?

18:45.045 --> 18:47.679
We built a fort!

18:47.681 --> 18:49.882
Are those my sheets?

18:49.884 --> 18:52.217
Yes, they are.

18:52.219 --> 18:53.619
Okay.

18:53.621 --> 18:55.320
Well, you kids have fun.

18:55.322 --> 18:56.655
I'm gonna go to sleep.

18:56.657 --> 18:59.291
Leonard, don't you want to see
the inside of the fort?

18:59.293 --> 19:00.592
Yeah, I'm good.

19:00.594 --> 19:01.927
Oh, come on.

19:01.929 --> 19:04.096
I really wanted to tell someone
they can't come in.

19:04.098 --> 19:05.797
Okay, fine.

19:05.799 --> 19:08.934
Sheldon, may I please
visit your fort?

19:08.936 --> 19:10.469
I want to say no,

19:10.471 --> 19:12.271
but it's too glorious.
Get in here!

19:14.419 --> 19:17.487
Thank you.
Okay, have a seat on the floor.

19:17.489 --> 19:19.021
SHELDON:
Not there. That's my spot.

